---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="About ReadForge">
  <section>
    <h2>About ReadForge</h2>
    <p>ReadForge is a local-first AI-powered book creation and reading application. It empowers you to create, manage, and read books generated with the help of Large Language Models (LLMs) like ChatGPT and Claude, while maintaining complete privacy and data ownership.</p>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üéØ Vision</h3>
      <p>We believe in:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Privacy First:</strong> Your data belongs to you, stored locally on your device</li>
        <li><strong>AI Augmentation:</strong> Use AI as a creative tool, not a replacement</li>
        <li><strong>Learning Focus:</strong> Track learning goals and purposes for each book</li>
        <li><strong>Accessibility:</strong> Multi-language support for users worldwide</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>‚ú® Core Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Flexible Book Creation:</strong> Optional fields for title, description, and learning purpose</li>
        <li><strong>AI Title Generation:</strong> Generate compelling book titles based on your content</li>
        <li><strong>Customizable AI Prompts:</strong> Control writing style, tone, and vocabulary</li>
        <li><strong>Multi-Language UI:</strong> English, Spanish, and Chinese support</li>
        <li><strong>Rich Reading Experience:</strong> Themes, highlights, notes, and bookmarks</li>
        <li><strong>Offline-First:</strong> Works completely offline after content generation</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üõ†Ô∏è Tech Stack</h3>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Framework:</strong> Flutter 3.10.1+ with Dart 3.10.1+</li>
        <li><strong>UI:</strong> Material Design 3</li>
        <li><strong>Database:</strong> Drift (SQLite) for local-first storage</li>
        <li><strong>State Management:</strong> Riverpod</li>
        <li><strong>Internationalization:</strong> Flutter l10n with ARB files</li>
        <li><strong>Build:</strong> Gradle 8.0+ with Java 17</li>
        <li><strong>CI/CD:</strong> GitHub Actions</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üîê Privacy & Security</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>‚úÖ 100% local data storage</li>
        <li>‚úÖ No cloud synchronization</li>
        <li>‚úÖ No user tracking or analytics</li>
        <li>‚úÖ No external API calls (except when you explicitly share prompts)</li>
        <li>‚úÖ Full data ownership and control</li>
        <li>‚úÖ Export your books anytime</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üåç Open Source</h3>
      <p>ReadForge is open source and welcomes contributions!</p>
      <p><a href="https://github.com/cmwen/read-forge-app" target="_blank" rel="noopener">View on GitHub ‚Üí</a></p>
      <p style="margin-top:1rem">Contributions welcome for:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>New language translations</li>
        <li>Bug fixes and improvements</li>
        <li>Feature suggestions</li>
        <li>Documentation</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>üìÑ License</h3>
      <p>MIT License - Free to use, modify, and distribute</p>
    </div>

    <div class="card">
      <h3>How this site works</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Source in <code>/astro</code></li>
        <li>Built with Astro and Startlight-inspired theme</li>
        <li>Deploys to GitHub Pages on release</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
